{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PNPYcZtUim45wz2ncn2sdR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I understand the current state:\n- 3-node RabbitMQ cluster running 3.12.14 on Erlang 25.3.2.15\n- StatefulSet using `rabbitmq:3.12-management` image\n- No PVCs - data is on emptyDir! This is important - the data is ephemeral.\n- The /app vhost exists with app-queue having 390 messages\n- I need to upgrade to RabbitMQ 4.1\n\nImportant observations:\nThe data volume is mounted as emptyDir, which means all queue data lives only in the current pods' memory. When pods restart during the upgrade, that data will be lost unless the RabbitMQ cluster replicates it across nodes. I need to be very careful with the rolling upgrade strategy to avoid losing those 390 messages in the queue.\n\nFor the 3.12 to 4.1 upgrade, there are some critical compatibility issues: RabbitMQ 4.0+ requires Erlang 26 while 3.12 uses Erlang 25, and classic mirrored queues were completely removed in 4.0 in favor of quorum queues. I need to check whether the queues are already quorum queues or if they're using the old mirrored queue setup, since that will determine the upgrade path and whether I need to migrate them first.\n\nThe bigger challenge with the emptyDir storage is that when pods restart during a rolling upgrade, they lose their local data—but in a 3-node cluster, as long as I upgrade one node at a time and maintain quorum, the queue data should persist across the cluster.\n\nI need to check what queue types are currently in use, since RabbitMQ 4.0 dropped support for classic mirrored queues entirely. If any exist, I'll need to convert them to quorum queues first. For the actual upgrade, I'd use the `rabbitmq:4.1-management` image, which requires Erlang 26 compatibility, then do a rolling update of the StatefulSet and verify the cluster stabilizes afterward.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1248,"cache_read_input_tokens":31000,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1248},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17fe7a5a-65fd-4eea-8779-ad7313d51734","uuid":"655f0384-0578-4541-99db-4410d3d2e6a3","request_id":"req_011CccyzRWqgzGwXGFdnMupL"}
