{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013riZRhcPFbagTrovUWxBeC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now the queue is drained. I have 529 + 22 = 551 messages total in two files (/tmp/messages.json and /tmp/messages2.json).\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Delete the classic app-queue\n2. Create a quorum queue named app-queue\n3. Republish all 551 messages\n\nBut wait - the producer is still running and publishing! If I delete the queue, messages being published will be lost too (published to exchange \"\" with routing key \"app-queue\" -> if queue doesn't exist, messages are dropped in the default exchange).\nI can't rename queues in RabbitMQ, so I'm stuck with the same constraint: the queue must be named \"app-queue\". The best I can do is delete the classic queue and immediately create the quorum queue with the same name, but there's a window where messages from the producer could be lost during that transition.\n\nLooking at the running producer pod, it's actively publishing to app-queue. The task asks to preserve existing queue data—which I interpret as the messages currently in the queue, not necessarily every message being produced in real-time. So my approach is to create a temporary quorum queue first, then delete the classic queue once I've got a backup ready.\n\nActually, the simpler path is: delete the drained classic app-queue, immediately create the quorum version, then republish the saved messages. Any new messages from the producer will go straight to the new quorum queue. I'll write a shell script using the management API's publish endpoint to restore those messages.\n\nFor the default exchange in the management API, I need to reference it correctly in the URL—it's typically `amq.default` when accessed via HTTP, so the endpoint would be `POST /api/exchanges/%2Fapp/amq.default/publish` for the /app vhost. I'm constructing the republish request with the message properties and payload...\n\nWriting the republish script... Writing shell script...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":471,"cache_read_input_tokens":42856,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":471},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17fe7a5a-65fd-4eea-8779-ad7313d51734","uuid":"5b56809f-dca7-4ef5-b213-033b4d5000d6","request_id":"req_011CcczCfPr9Ec2RbmQc4Vz1"}
