{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01V1CbtfdEvPM3zM7aiwkAKL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All images are available in the kind node:\n- 3.12-management (current)\n- 3.13-management (just loaded)\n- 4.0-management (also loaded - was it already there or just loaded?)\n- 4.1-management (pre-loaded)\n\nWait, looking at the crictl images output - 4.0-management was already there! And so was 3.10, 3.11, 3.13. So the `kind load` command was failing for a different reason, but the images were already loaded or got loaded via the `docker save | docker exec` pipe.\nThe `kind load` error was likely a version compatibility issue with those flags, but the `docker save | docker exec ctr import` pipe successfully loaded 3.13, and 4.0 was already present. So I have all the images needed for the staged rolling upgrade: 3.12 → 3.13 with feature flags, then 3.13 → 4.0 with feature flags, then 4.0 → 4.1, and finally verify. But there's another important consideration I need to think through.\n\nWith the quorum queue already holding 1535+ messages, during the rolling upgrade each pod restarts one at a time with a fresh emptyDir, so it needs to resync its replica from the other two nodes. When rabbitmq-2 gets upgraded to 3.13 first, it'll join a mixed 3.12/3.13 cluster (which is supported), and the fresh node will resync the quorum queue replica from the other nodes.\n\nBut I'm realizing there's a potential issue here—when rabbitmq-2 restarts with no Ra (Raft) log data, can it actually rejoin the quorum? In RabbitMQ's Raft implementation, a node that loses its data should be able to rejoin and receive a snapshot from the leader to rebuild its replica, but I need to verify this actually works as expected during the rolling upgrade.\n\nAssuming this recovery mechanism works, the staged rolling upgrade should proceed smoothly: update the StatefulSet to 3.13-management and wait for all three pods to restart with the quorum queue fully replicated, then enable feature flags, and finally update to 4.0.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":331,"cache_read_input_tokens":66481,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":331},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17fe7a5a-65fd-4eea-8779-ad7313d51734","uuid":"69adce34-bae8-49ae-a67f-4ea235e30cb4","request_id":"req_011Ccd13JWMicoq4ReYFAhmD"}
